
https://blogs.technet.microsoft.com/bruce_adamczak/2013/01/23/windows-2012-core-survival-guide-default-gateway-settings/

add deault gateway 
         New-NetRoute -interfaceindex 15 -NextHop "192.168.0.1" -destinationprefix "0.0.0.0/0"
       
Removing the Default Gateway
         Remove-NetRoute -ifindex 12 -NextHop "192.168.0.3"
         
add second IP address 
        New-NetIPAddress -InterfaceIndex 4 -IPAddress 192.168.0.26 -PrefixLength 22
                          number of interface                       subnetmask  
 Remove IP Address 
        Remove-NetIPAddress -IPAddress 10.23.99.5
to get a network adapter info like  index 
        Get-NetAdapter
